# CLAUDE.md — Personal Additions (Example)

> This is a worked example of a CLAUDE.local.md. Copy templates/CLAUDE.local.md.template
> to ~/.claude/CLAUDE.local.md and edit. Below shows what a real one might look like.

## My Setup

- Primary machine: MacBook Pro M3 Max
- Secondary: Linux desktop (Fedora)
- Cloud: Vercel for hosting, Supabase for DB, Notion for docs
- Time zone: Europe/Berlin

## My Active Projects Index

- **app-alpha**: `~/code/app-alpha` — Next.js 15 App Router, primary product
- **infra-prod**: `~/code/infra-prod` — Terraform for AWS
- **personal-site**: `~/code/personal-site` — Astro + Tailwind

## Personal Behavioral Tweaks

- Always run `pnpm` not `npm` in this user's repos
- Never run `terraform destroy` on infra-prod without an extra prompt
- When editing Notion-bound routines, always update both Notion ID env var AND the routine
